news.title: Court denies HDIL’s promoter permission to travel to Hyderabad, but can visit other places
news.para: A special court refused Sarang Wadhawan's request to visit Hyderabad due to a pending threat investigation. Wadhawan faces money laundering charges. The court permitted him to travel to Tamil Nadu, Goa, and Uttarakhand for religious reasons. He can also visit NCR for legal consultations.

news.title: China Evergrande Group delisted from Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: Shares in heavily indebted China Evergrande Group were taken off the Hong Kong Stock Exchange on Monday, capping a grim reversal of fortune for the once-booming property developer. The statement added that China Evergrande Group was a holding company and that liquidators had assumed control of more than 100 companies within the group.

news.title: 360 ONE Asset acquires 50% stake in Bluegrass Business Park in Pune for ₹2,400 crore
news.para: 360 ONE Asset procured a 50% stake in Bluegrass Business Park. The acquisition was made from Brookfield Asset Management. The business park is a two million sq ft office development. It is located in Kalyani Nagar, Pune. The deal was valued at approximately ₹2,400 crore. Brookfield will continue to manage the asset. They will also oversee development and leasing.

news.title: HUDCO plans to raise up to ₹3,000 crore through debentures
news.para: HUDCO is set to raise up to Rs 3,000 crore through non-convertible debentures, approved by the Board of Directors as part of a larger Rs 65,000 crore bond issuance plan for 2025-26. The decision comes after the company reported a 13% increase in consolidated net profit for the first quarter and declared an interim dividend.

news.title: Krrish Realtech diverted ₹205-crore homebuyers' fund for Colombo hotel: ED
news.para: A Gurugram-based realty group, Krrish Realtech, defrauded home buyers. The group collected over Rs 500 crore for housing plots. However, they diverted Rs 205 crore to a Sri Lanka hotel project. The Enforcement Directorate (ED) is investigating Amit Katyal and others. Katyal is already arrested in another case. The ED filed a chargesheet and the court issued a notice.

news.title: Gaurs Group acquires 12-acre land at Yamuna Expressway
news.para: Gaurs Group has expanded its portfolio with the acquisition of a 12-acre land parcel along the Yamuna Expressway, earmarked for a new residential project. The company plans to invest ₹1,400 crore in developing high-rise, ultra-luxury residences, anticipating a topline of ₹2,000 crore.

news.title: India’s highest selling market - Pune sells 44,000 new homes in January-June 2025: Data expert Rahul Ajmera decodes the trends
news.para: Pune continues to outpace other metro cities with record sales of new homes, driven by affordable pricing and dual IT+Manufacturing economy

news.title: Illegal constructions razed in urban areas of Panchkula
news.para: In Panchkula, the District Town Planner (DTP) recently conducted a significant enforcement drive, demolishing 15 unauthorized DPC constructions in Barona Khud village. These actions were taken after serving prior notices to defaulters who failed to remove the illegal structures.

news.title: India's 28-listed builders sell properties worth ₹53,000 crore in April-June 2025
news.para: India's listed real estate companies witnessed robust sales, reaching nearly Rs 53,000 crore in the April-June quarter, driven by strong residential demand. Prestige Estates led with the highest sales bookings, followed by DLF and Godrej Properties. These top five developers contributed significantly to the total sales, indicating a concentrated market benefiting from increased homebuyer confidence.

news.title: Microsoft takes up 2.64 lakh sq ft office in Hyderabad at ₹5.4 crore per month
news.para: Microsoft India (R&D) has leased 264,000 sq ft in Hyderabad's financial district from Table Space Technologies, commencing July 2025. The five-year lease at Phoenix Centaurus involves a monthly rent of ₹1.77 crore, escalating annually by 4.8%. This expansion highlights Hyderabad's appeal to large tech companies due to its talent pool and infrastructure.

news.title: Altum Credo raises ₹170 crore from British International Investment
news.para: British International Investment (BII) has invested ₹170 crore in Altum Credo Home Finance, an affordable housing finance company. This funding will enable Altum Credo to expand operations within India and strengthen its IT infrastructure.

news.title: Maharashtra REAT overturns unilateral possession date extension by MahaRERA
news.para: The Maharashtra Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (MREAT) overturned MahaRERA's order extending the possession date for a Navi Mumbai project, deeming unilateral extensions without homebuyers' consent unlawful. MREAT directed the promoter, Supreme Construction and Developers, to pay interest to homebuyers Neha and Nitin Walavalkar from January 2018, rejecting claims of Covid-related delays and MMRDA infrastructure issues as force majeure.

news.title: Chamarajanagar ZP survey identifies 35,050 houseless, 4,471 site-less families in 2024-25
news.para: Chamarajanagar zilla panchayat's recent survey for 2024-25 identified 35,050 houseless and 4,471 site-less families, recommending house construction under government schemes. Chamarajanagar and Gundlupet taluks have the highest number of houseless families. The survey used GPS-based verification to ensure genuine beneficiaries, with varying grants provided based on category, as the ZP awaits approval for housing allotments.

news.title: Telangana RERA puts R Homes project in abeyance for violating norms
news.para: TG RERA has put R Homes Infra's Jai Vasavis Bliss Heights project on hold due to complaints of misrepresentation and RERA violations. The firm allegedly collected funds pre-launch with false assurances and failed to file mandatory progress reports. RERA has frozen bank accounts and halted marketing activities, demanding a response from R Homes to avoid penalties.

news.title: Can’t let MLA interfere in redevelopment: Bombay HC to SRA, BMC
news.para: The Bombay High Court has intervened in a Vile Parle slum rehabilitation project, restricting the SRA and BMC from external interference. BJP MLA Parag Alavani and a rival developer were found to be unduly influencing the scheme, causing delays and hindering the approved redevelopment plan by Sateri Builders.

news.title: Nine years on, housing project stuck, homebuyers allege fraud in Gurugram
news.para: Over 100 homebuyers protested against Ocean Seven Buildtech in Gurugram, alleging fraud and diversion of funds in their Sector 109 housing project. The developer assures possession by March 2026, blaming delays on buyer protests and fund issues, while an EOW investigation is underway.

news.title: Taxman may get more power to demolish benami realty deals
news.para: To combat benami property deals, a CBDT panel suggests stricter measures, including access to Aadhaar data and property registries. The recommendations aim to identify 'dummy directors' in shell companies and confiscate other assets if benami properties are untraceable. These steps seek to address loopholes and ambiguities in the existing law, enhancing the I-T department's ability to tackle benami transactions.

news.title: DDA to e-auction over 200 properties including festival event sites, cafes
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has launched an e-auction featuring over 200 premium properties, including function sites, kiosks, and cafes, available on a license-fee basis. This initiative aims to provide additional event spaces during the upcoming festive season. Registration begins August 26, with e-auctions starting September 30, offering opportunities for various commercial ventures across Delhi.

news.title: NCLAT sets aside plea against Nuvoco Vistas acquisition of Vadraj Cement
news.para: The NCLAT has upheld the acquisition of Vadraj Cement by Nuvoco Vistas, dismissing a plea challenging the resolution plan. The tribunal affirmed the NCLT's approval of Nuvoco's bid, which includes an upfront payment of Rs 1,800 crore.

news.title: Thane civic body forms special squad to curb unauthorised constructions
news.para: The Thane Municipal Corporation has established a special squad to combat the rising number of illegal constructions in Diva and Mumbra, following numerous complaints. Commissioner Saurabh Rao ordered the team's formation after a review meeting, highlighting the urgency to address these violations.
